"""
# Spec — `common_compression_framework`

Scenario REQ-006/REQ-007: shared API round-trips supported codecs
  Given a caller selects `std.common.compress`
  When bytes are compressed and then decompressed through the same API
  Then the original payload is returned

Scenario REQ-009: LZ4 block mode requires explicit hint on decode
  Given a raw LZ4 block without frame magic
  When the caller supplies `CompressionCodec.lz4`
  Then decode succeeds

Scenario REQ-010: Zstd emitted frames are host-tool interoperable for the delivered subset
  Given bytes encoded into a standard raw/RLE zstd frame
  When host `zstd` decodes the frame
  Then the payload bytes match

Scenario REQ-011: XZ/LZMA2 emitted streams are host-tool interoperable for the delivered subset
  Given bytes encoded into a standard single-filter XZ/LZMA2 stream
  When host `xz` decodes the stream
  Then the payload bytes match

Scenario REQ-012: malformed data fails closed
  Given truncated or corrupted framed bytes
  When the decoder runs
  Then it returns a typed compression error
"""
